comment.narrative:
[o] 3 BUR submitted to UNFCCC;
[p] Specific studies carried out to address the insufficient data about sector specific climate impacts and their economic implications as well as apparent deficit in climate related economic analysis, including damage and loss analysis, especially at the local level;
[r] Vulnerability and adaptation analyses finalized using nexus approach;
[s] More in-depth gender analyses carried out to better understand how climate change impacts men and women as well as their different vulnerabilities to climate risks and the ways in which they seek to adapt to climate change;
[t] The level of climate change inclusion in the education curricula in the country assessed.

[h] 3BUR compiled, adopted by the Government and submitted to UNFCCC;
[i] The process of establishment of the domestic Measurement, Reporting and Verification arrangements supported;
[j] New case studies developed to capture main energy consumer in summer: Green cooling scenario;
[k] Extreme climate events modelled for the country and for selected city/region;
[l] Vulnerability and adaptation in various sectors assessed, identifying the bottlenecks and recommend actions for improvement;
[m] Targeted public awareness activities implemented, following the results and recommendations of the public awareness survey
[n] More in-depth gender activities carried out as per the draft national gender and climate change action plan, to better understand the implications for men and women of relevant mitigation actions, policies or programmes.
